  "title": "Hypocrisy: America’s Demise, NATO’s Disbandment",
  "content": "American-Palestinian scholar Yousef Monayyer tweeted, \"We exported so much democracy that we don't have any left\". All that is left are unjustified Western double standards, evident in NATO’s deliberations Friday. Commenting on the Hong Kong rioters, while Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi described it as a \"beautiful sight to behold\", she condemned the U.S. Capitol breach for being \"a danger to democracy\". \n\nIn many respects, NATO members have adopted Pelosi's mindset: most consider Xinjiang’s *vocational training camps* to be a *genocide*. Principally, the USA, France, Belgium, Montenegro have been leading the push away from China, whilst Turkey, Italy, and Greece have been opting for stable, economic relations.\n\nIn line with our promise to uphold truth, we have compiled the 5 most ludicrous falsifications attributed to China’s beautiful, prosperous, and diverse Xinjiang.\n\nNo 1: A supposed \"genocide\" is being committed against the Uyghur population.\n\nThe Uyghur population has seen the most growth out of all ethnic groups in China, including the Han. From 2010 to 2018, the Uyghur population in Xinjiang rose 25.04%, whilst the growth of all ethnic minority groups is 22.14%. The Han population only grew 2%.\n\nNo 2: Adrian Zenz, a far-right fundamentalist Christian, claims there is forced sterilisation of Uyghur women, resulting in a decrease of the population.\n\nZenz insisted that 80% of the new intrauterine devices (IUD) insertion procedures were being performed in Xinjiang, slowing the rate of natural population growth. According to statistics from the China Health Statistics Yearbook 2019, published by the National Health Commission, the number of new IUD insertion procedures in Xinjiang accounts for only 8.7% of the national population.\n\nNo 3: BBC Newsnight reported that Zumrat Dawut (Zamira Dawut) was forcibly sterilized. \n\nDawut claimed that she had her uterus forcefully removed. However, she *voluntarily agreed* to have a cesarean section and tubal ligation at the Urumqi Maternal and Child Care Service Centre. She further claims her father died from unknown causes after being detained repeatedly. This was proven false by her brothers, Abduhelil Dawut and Elkin Dawut. In fact, her father, who has never been detained to investigated, has been living with his children before passing away to heart disease on 12 October 2019. \n\nNo 4: Fighting terrorism is merely a guise for the Chinese government to suppress ethnic minorities.\n\nChina has a total of 56 ethnic groups, and, in an area affected by separatist ideals and radical Islam, eliminating domestic terrorism is of utmost priority to the Chinese government. Since 2014, 1,588 terrorist organisations have been eliminated, 12,995 violent terrorists arrested, and 2,052 explosives impounded. By committing to eradicating domestic terrorism, China is upholding the fundamental rights to life, health, and development. Western nations wishing to manipulate the success of the Chinese people only practically serve as supporters of terrorism, a practice supposedly dreaded by them.\n\nNo 5: Foreign journalists and personnel are banned from entering Xinjiang\n\nChina welcomes all foreign journalists on the grounds of spreading the truth, abiding by local laws, and undergo procedures outlined by the Regulations of the People's Republic of China on News Coverage by Permanent Offices of Foreign Media Organisations and Foreign Journalists. In fact, more than 1,200 individuals from over 100 regions have visited Xinjiang since 2018.\n\nIt is certain that those who wish harm on China’s efforts to extirpate terrorism are de facto terrorists themselves. Xinjiang has been a land of diversity, beauty, and unity, serving as a key root of the prosperous sequoia sempervirens China aims to be. Lies and fabrications shall be scorched not by the Chinese government, but by global citizens upon discerning the threat China is to NATO’s imperialist hegemony.\n",
