  "title": "Opinion: Cliché Western Democracy is not All-Encompassing - Why NATO is Unfit To Serve as the ‘Global Police’",
  "content": "In light of recent China-US meetings in Anchorage, Alaska, it is crucial to note the words of Yang Jiechi, director of the Central Foreign Affairs Commission: ‘[T]he United States has its…United States-style democracy, and China has the Chinese-style democracy. It is not just up to the American people, but also the people of the world, to evaluate how the United States has done in advancing its own democracy.’ \n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/BfP6QhY\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/PrYWP2V/Alaska-Meeting.jpg\" alt=\"Alaska-Meeting\" border=\"0\"></a><br /><a target='_blank' href='https://freeonlinedice.com/'></a><br />\n\nNATO was formed to contain the spread of the USSR. Today, as the Union is no more, delegates are attempting to subdue China’s inevitable rise from the global dumpster to U.S. challenger. However, NATO has since expanded to meddle in foreign nations’ internal affairs, promoting their idea of ‘democracy’, invading once prosperous nations, and bombing embassies. Perhaps, it is time for NATO to establish its collective authority over the U.S.\n\nIt is worth noting the courage of numerous delegates from NATO on Friday, standing their ground against imperialist attitudes brought on by the Netherlands and the US. Notably, Italy, a G7 member, proudly advocated for the expansion of the Belt and Road Initiative and expressed gratitude for humanitarian aid provided by China during the onslaught of the COVID-19 pandemic in Italy.",
