  "title": "Opinion: Cooperation amidst Confusion; Virtue-Signalling over Economic Livelihood - NATO’s Dilemma",
  "content": "Jealousy, carefully enshrined as Othello’s hubris, is emerging once more. With the advancement of China’s 5G network, Western nations are attempting in vain to contain China, accusing China of conducting espionage, cyber-attacks, and infringing on human rights. What many nations under the American camp of NATO failed to recognise on Saturday is the economic lifeline China serves for many developing nations. Nevertheless, those who favour economic substance over political games, like Turkey, Italy, and Greece, have seen tremendous national growth and increased free trade. China has aided in many nations’ paying of debts, and improving trade linkages, lowering otherwise fixed costs of transportation. As a result, these defiant nations rose up to form the Virtually Meeting Underdeveloped Nations bloc, suspiciously shortened to VMUN. Accordingly, the title of Jane Austen’s great novel, Pride and Prejudice, is reinforced. North Macedonia eloquently put: ‘We cannot let our ***prejudice*** against China affect a great trade plan.’ \n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/F0JD1Dq\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/4YMVLVg/5G-China.jpg\" alt=\"5G-China\" border=\"0\"></a><br /><a target='_blank' href='https://dedupelist.com/'>\n\nTruthfully, those remarks were generous. Western nations under severe political pressure from the United States also evoke a sense of ***pride*** as these nations are disillusioned to believe US democracy is fit for all. To oppose China, these nations have proposed a NATO Belt and Road Initiative, essentially appropriating President Xi Jinping’s signature plan under the guise of democracy. However, it is evident to developing nations that the US initiatives come with strict conditions, those bullying nations into smearing China on a global stage. Contrarily, China has been unconditional with the providing of economic and social aid, as seen during the pandemic.",
  "author": "xinhua",
