  "title": "Italy Blasts the Netherlands for Prioritising Political Image over Economic Lifeline",
  "content": "The thin, easily penetrable style of Macbeth led to the exposing of his lack of substance. Analogously, nations like the Netherlands have been overwhelmed by their unwavering will to preserve their national dignity under the hegemonic American system, often gliding over the inherent economic issues. Nonetheless, those nations with the slightest ***sense and sensibility***, including Turkey, Bulgaria, Greece, and Hungary, have recognised China’s role in their domestic development, GDP growth, and international cooperation.\n\nThe One Belt One Road is a global infrastructure initiative led by China’s Xi Jinping, which aims to ‘to construct a unified large market and make full use of both international and domestic markets, through cultural exchange and integration, to enhance mutual understanding and trust of member nations, resulting in an innovative pattern of capital inflows, talent pools, and technology databases’. It further strives to improve education, real estate, power grids, and overall construction investments along the former trade routes, notably the Silke Road, and those of Marco Polo, Ibn Battuta, and Zheng He. As of 2017, The Belt and Road Initiative covered more than 68 countries, 65% of the global population, and over 40% of the global GDP. Its impacts transcend the economy. During the initial stages of the pandemic, Italy received humanitarian support from China in multiple forms. \n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/6FN3ZsD\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/pdntPX4/One-belt-one-road-svg.png\" alt=\"One-belt-one-road-svg\" border=\"0\">\n\nRegardless of clear, global benefits, many Western nations choose to preserve their political affiliations over the values of their citizens, ones who feel the imminent impacts of economic withering.",
