  "title": "Opinion: Lobbyists To Command Governments Globally - Blocked by Unlikely Alliance",
  "content": "*This article reflects the opinions of the author, not necessarily those of Xinhua.*\n\nDISEC’s Saturday proposals have been shaky. Iraq’s solution of utilising private hackers to host training courses for government cybersecurity personnel comes with the potential of the eradication of a people’s government, turning it into one dominated by corporate tech giants. Regardless of political ideology, a government must represent its citizens through its own sacrifices. The Iraqi bloc’s plan assured lukewarm delegates that individual hackers, upon completing background checks, would not gain information to sensitive data. This works fair-and-square until the moment it is implemented. With increased government dependency on individuals and corporations to train government officials on hacking, the interests of said groups would be catered towards, devaluing what the West broadcasts as democracy. Through efforts made by an Iran-US bloc, the draft resolution failed to succeed, reassuring the global community of cyber-secure governments.\n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/qgKvF32\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/DMhZgHj/Hacker-computer-cyber-security.jpg\" alt=\"Hacker-computer-cyber-security\" border=\"0\">\n\nIt is impossible to see why governments are unwilling to spend money themselves to combat cybercrime, especially considering governments are often victims. This is not a time to promote decentralised behaviour. Global governments need to rise to face the dangers of the dark web as opposed to relying on civilians. A concentrated government can efficiently and effectively carry out operations as seen in President Xi’s war on corruption. It is of particular interest to western laggards to ramp up efforts to eradicate major cyber threats once and for all. \n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/JCsgZtj\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/g6RhY9Z/Anti-Corruption-China.jpg\" alt=\"Anti-Corruption-China\" border=\"0\"></a><br /><a target='_blank' href='https://imgbb.com/'>\n\n*Nonetheless, Xinhua would like to commend the Assistant Director of DISEC in particular for his eloquent adjectives.*",
