  "title": "Syrian Terrorist Group Attacks Civilians: Greece Borders Overwhelmed with Refugees",
  "content": "(CNN) – Civilians on the western borders face a tremendous terror at this time. An unidentified terrorist group originating from Syria has systematically launched attacks on innocent citizens, leading to refugees fleeing from the west across the Mediterranean. Having reached the borders of Greece, refugee camps have become overcrowded and unable to accommodate the mass influx of refugees. \n\nSyria’s government has responded to the crisis by stating that they do not have any connection to the terrorist group, and believes the group is being funded by a foreign government. Most delegates agree upon the proposal to relocate asylum seekers; however at this point only Italy and Portugal has agreed to take in refugees. Under the circumstances, Ireland proposed to investigate further into the terrorist group, which had also been discussed earlier in the crisis. No further information is available on this terrorist group at the moment. \n\nItaly proposes to collaborate with the Syrian government to find access to communications and gain access to the terrorist group. Preparation towards accommodating the refugees have been made with a public directive planning transportation methods. Contrasting opinions surround this public directive, as resources currently are being spread thin. Notions surrounding providing humanitarian aid to the current refugees is also a matter of discussion. Greater progress is in the works by the delegates. On that note, a new crisis update has been made available: several overcrowded refugee sites have been attacked, bombed, and hostages have been taken; and the delegates must immediately take action.\n",
