  "title": "WHO Will Stop this Plague (?) ",
  "content": "**Currently, in the world, the global trade of live animals has quadrupled in the last 50 years, causing more than two billion animals to be transported each year. **\n\nAlthough this is the case, there is a severe lack of oversight as well as regulation for these live animals. However, not only this but poorly conditioned farms have also created the spreading of a global disease. Scientists have also found a mysterious infection that has caused over 43% of the cattle population to die. Many of these countries believe the two, most important things to do right now are to, first find the origin of this disease, and second, contain this disease and make sure they stay there. Ultimately, the countries have similar ideas on how to tackle this problem.\n\nNow, the problem for these delegates is, what will their first step be? Individual delegates are debating over whether they should first invest in the roots of this disease or contain this disease. People are already trying to get others to become a signatory for them as well as found out what was the cause for this problem. Cows were being used by an unknown organization to cause chaos and disease. Now, the problem is, how will the members of WHO take on this problem? \n\nGoing into this problem, it has appeared that two of these members in this unknown group are from Saudi Arabia, while one is from Brazil. \n\nOrigins of this disease are still being found, and Japan wants to lead this research; yet with furious debate, the members of WHO is running out of time. \n",
