  "title": "UNEP Crisis - Challenge 1 ",
  "content": "Columbia is in a crisis. Amazon river and the Indigenous village besides it have suffered governmental land mismanagement. How could we be so heartless and ignore this issue? Self-reliance is what these tribes have prided themselves on for centuries but now they’re forced to trade with nearby towns, which completely crushes that aspect of their sacred culture. \n\n\tMen and women in tribes feel disconnected with their culture, ancestors and practices. Unity and simplicity is what keeps these tribes together, what keeps them alive. Never before have we seen the Amazon river starting to slow down, making us realise how big of an issue this actually is. \n\n\tIn Columbia, the pressure is on the government to fix what they’ve started. People are angry and distraught. Countries from all around have come together to debate solution ideas. Nature doesn’t wait, therefore the clock is ticking. Going from argument to argument, countries such as Haiti and Norway are determined to help Brazil and voice their concerns on the seriousness of this issue. Overall, it is time to find an effective solution that could be put in place as soon as possible. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
