  "title": "US SENATE CRISIS LIVE UPDATE 3",
  "content": "*The following text contains large words required by the directors of the IPC. Those with **hippopotomonstrosesquippedaliophobia** are advised to refrain from reading. Contact a medical professional if necessary.*\n\nThe **soi-disant** Senator Amy Klobuchar claims that they are almost done writing their directive to shut down injection sites to protect the American people. She is currently looking for co-sponsors to her directive.\n\nGiven that a crisis is at hand, the Senate is less **obstreperous** than it was when discussing its regular topics yesterday. In fact, it seems that they have found a common ground, devoid of devious partisan **taradiddles** and mutterings.\n\nTo further facilitate the progress of the committee, Co-Director Othman Mekhloufi allows the committee to forgo collecting sponsors for their directives. When there are more drugs per capita in all of America than there were in **Lollapalooza** during the summer of 2012, standard crisis procedures must be shed in order to increase decision making efficacy.\n\nDirectives are now being passed. One called “Operation Safe Bamboo,” which calls for drug testing next to safe consumption sites meets widespread acclaim from the committee. Additionally, a directive from Klobuchar and Cruz—a bipartisan bill that even Co-Director Mekhloufi says “frankly does not need any debate—also “overwhelmingly passes.” Only time will tell what the outcomes of these motions will be.\n",
