  "content": "Amongst a committee with constant accusations of delegates promoting ***taradiddles***, they have finally managed to invite a manager of the bursted dam. It is alleged that the company originated from China although they are not affiliated with the government. They claim the dam was built to venerate a god. A ***soi-distant*** delegate sent an amateur scientist to collect rock samples from the dam, which accidentally resulted in its bursting. \n\nIn the Q&A section, some ***lollapalooza*** questions were asked despite not gaining much useful information. Brazil has reasserted the importance of the economy over indigenous rights, noting they will aid Haiti in efforts to continue with the dams, increase military presence, and enforce crackdowns. Haiti has been convinced to be converted to venerate this supposedly almighty god. Russia, on the other hand, has become moderate, whilst China reaffirms its independence from the corporation building dams. \n\nNonetheless, it still seems that all delegates have ***hippopotomonstrosesquippedaliophobia***, the fear of long words. Many longer words have more complex meanings, reducing the need for overall modifiers. But, due to this fear, delegates have been constrained to lengthy speeches and directives. It is uncertain if Haiti’s veneration of the supposed god would be short-lived as a result of length.\n",
