  "title": "Facebook: The Final Battle with Tencent",
  "content": "In the first regular committee session after the morning crisis, members of Facebook are presenting a slideshow with ideas such as revamping Facebook and adding new features to clash against Tencent. \n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/fnYP23G\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/LJz28Th/shutterstock-186292982a.jpg\" alt=\"shutterstock-186292982a\" border=\"0\"></a>\n\nThe Chinese business that dominates the gaming industry and owns WeChat has always been a competitor with Facebook. Facebook sees Tencent as a threat, always trying to compete against them. In the committee, the members have finally concluded with short-term and long-term solutions to win against Tencent. \n\nTencent has always been a threat to the current and future of Facebook; government privacy laws do not limit Tencent, legally permitting their creators and designers to expedite the design-thinking process. \n\nOn the other hand, Facebook cannot expand into China as it is problematic due to the laws the government has on privacy for outsiders. Yet, Facebook can grow worldwide, while it appears that it is mostly only in China. In their slideshow, they have Now, as Mark Zuckerberg has said, “the main revenue of Facebook comes from advertisements.” \n\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/jM75r7p\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/J7XdsXh/Facebook-ads-guide-for-beginners-costa-del-sol-marbella-estepona-manilva-sanpedro-fuengirola.jpg\" alt=\"Facebook-ads-guide-for-beginners-costa-del-sol-marbella-estepona-manilva-sanpedro-fuengirola\" border=\"0\"></a>)\n\nThe next step Facebook will take is to start making a transaction system. This transaction system will be partnered with both Paypal and Linkedin and named “Facebook Pay.” Facebook Pay will also act as a bank for people to store their money in. This will help attract more users to Facebook overall. After this, they plan on making platform integrations. They are going to add shopping and other new features to Facebook. Finally, they plan to revamp the current UI system of Facebook and start investments and research in both VR and AR. Not only this, but they plan to get more partnerships, make lifestyle changes, try to draw in younger generations, and finally increase transparency and inform the public about the data usage. \n\nUltimately, we here at the British Broadcasting Corporation would like to congratulate the members of Facebook for successfully making these decisions. \n\n\n",
